CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 27, 1958, pg. 3, reads: "Repair Not Made - Despite Meyer M. Talenfeld's boast on Dec. 23, at Alderman Leonard Civill's office that repairs at 64 Arthur St. had been made, a City Health Department official later said that this was not so, and the property which contains scores of tenants must be repaired. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Three story brick building with drive-in addition on side and billboard for Liberty Beverage Company, 64 Arthur Street, Hill District
